What Does the BBBT/SunTrust merger of equals mean for bank stocks? Now up on @realmoney @jimcramer @tomkeene @TeamCavuto Who's Next? Probably No One! * The bank merger is a one off and is a very modest negative for the existing and large money center banks

BB&T and Sun Trust have announced a $66 billion merger of equals intended to create the country's sixth largest bank. streetinsider.com/Corporate+… While there will likely be a hostile political reaction (from left of center Democrats) I expect the deal to go through. 131

I dont expect this transaction to have a domino impact on an acceleration of large deals nor do I expect the announcement to impact bank stocks today. In fact, the creation of another large and more efficient bank could be seen as a very slight negative for our holdings of the

three money center banks, Citigroup, BankAmerica and Wells Fargo. While bank competitors in the mid-atlantic and southern areas may feel some pressure in the markets over the next few days, it will likely be offset by merger speculation. $C $BAC
Generally, I have recently suggested that bank stock prices will cool off a bit. realmoney.thestreet.com/doug… @jimcramer @tomkeene @andrewrsorkin @beckyquick @SquawkCNBC
